# Links and Images

## Inline Links

A simple link: [Visit Example](https://example.com)

Link with formatting: [_Emphasized_ link text](https://example.com)

Link with path: [Example Site](https://example.com/page)

## Reference Links

You can define references separately for cleaner text.

First define the reference:

[example]: https://example.com

Then use it: [Click here][example] for the example site.

## Autolinks

Direct URLs: <https://example.com>

Email addresses: <user@example.com>

## Images

### Inline Images

![Alt text](image.jpg)

![Logo](logo.png)

### Reference Images

![Profile Picture][profile]

![Avatar][]

[profile]: profile.jpg
[Avatar]: avatar.png

## Links with Attributes

Add IDs, classes, or custom attributes to links:

[Example Link](https://example.com){#main-link .external}

## Combining Links and Images

Clickable image (link with image as text):

[![Alt text](thumbnail.jpg)](full-image.jpg)

## Footnote References

Basic text with a footnote reference[^1].

Another footnote[^note] can have any label.

[^1]: This is the footnote content.
[^note]: This is another footnote with a custom label.

## Symbols

You can use emoji-style symbols: :smile: :heart: :rocket:

Custom symbols: :arrow_right: :warning: :check_mark:
